  "text": "kinase complex and undergoes a rapid conformational change, allowing its homo-dimerization and nuclear translocation where it binds to the interferon-stimulated response elements of the target genes. [CITATION_1] The important role of IRF3 in the induction of interferon responses suggests that it must be appropriately regulated and \"finely tuned\" to determine the accurate nature of the final innate immune responses. [CITATION_2] On the other hand, cancer cells might hijack these regulatory mechanisms or even develop novel strategies to block the interferon responses, in fulfilling the escape of the immune surveillance.",
